The paper deals with clustering and classification techniques, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and data mining fields. The use of a Sentenced Discrepancy Measure and the modification of K-MEANS++ and kNN algorithms suggest a focus on the areas of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The issue of incomplete data characterization due to missing attributes is a common problem in data mining, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The theoretical analysis and experiments conducted in the paper also suggest a focus on data mining (cs.DM) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
